title: Empanadas de Jamon, Queso, y Huevo Duro (Ham, Cheese, and Hard-boiled Egg Empanadas)

Directions.1: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Grease 2 baking sheets with cooking spray.

Directions.2: Combine ham, Gouda cheese, and hard-boiled eggs in a bowl; mix well.

Directions.3: Arrange pastry disks on a flat surface; dab a little water around the rims. Place a large tablespoonful of ham and cheese mixture in the center; fold pastry over and press edge with a fork to seal well.

Directions.4: Place empanadas on the prepared baking sheets. Brush with beaten egg.

Directions.5: Bake in the preheated oven until golden, 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool for 5 minutes before serving.
